The brush embroidery technique is one of my favorites because it's so versatile. You can change the colors and style of the flowers to work for any occasion. 

These brush embroidery cookies were inspired by a handbag that I bought for my mom while visiting Spain a few years ago. 

See the full tutorial and get the supply list and recipes for this project on Patreon. 
https://www.patreon.com/posts/brush-cookies-46789186

I made two other cookies - one for each of my daughters - which I'll be sharing soon 😄

The brush embroidery technique is one of my favorites because it's so versatile. You can change the colors and style of the flowers to work for any occasion. 

These brush embroidery cookies were inspired by a handbag that I bought for my mom while visiting Spain a few years ago. 

See the full tutorial and get the supply list and recipes for this project on Patreon. 
https://www.patreon.com/posts/brush-cookies-46789186

node.text:
I used two different methods of applying the base layer of icing on these brush embroidery cookies. Can you see the difference between the flowers on the round and hexagon cookies?

The full tutorial and recipes are available to my all-access and VIP subscribers on Patreon.

https://www.patreon.com/posts/new-premium-7a-54174457
